# StudyBuddy — General Rules

## Project overview

StudyBuddy is a Flask-based educational app with AI-powered study tools (summaries, flashcards, tutoring, homework help, assessments). It uses MongoDB, Celery/RabbitMQ workers, and supports OpenAI and Gemini.

## Stack

- Python 3.11, Flask, Gunicorn
- MongoDB, Celery, RabbitMQ
- Jinja2 templates under `ui/templates/`
- Services in `src/services/`, tests in `tests/`

## Coding guidelines

- Match existing patterns in the file you are editing.
- Keep changes minimal and focused on the requested task.
- Prefer extending existing services over adding parallel implementations.
- Run relevant tests after substantive changes (`pytest tests/`).
- Do not commit secrets; use `.env` for configuration.

